name: Pygmy Vole Muntjac (Muntiacus brevissimus)
description: At 30 mm long, the pygmy vole muntjac is one of the smaller mammals and by far the tiniest ungulate. Translucent hide covers its bony spinal carapace. It sports no horns and its limbs end in sharp nibs of keratin (that would be hooves in larger species) which allow it to chase at a rapid gait after land-based krill.
